data.description:
Incredible end unit townhome located within blocks of the West Center GVR Rec Center. It is move-in ready! With tile countertops in the kitchen, satillo tile throughout, and stacked washer/dryer. Step outside to the beautiful community courtyard, a tranquil oasis where you can unwind and relax in the fresh air. With the HOA including roof maintenance, garbage, pool, spa, and common grounds maintenance, you are free to enjoy all the amenities this fabulous community has to offer. Call today for a private showing! Aptly named, Green Valley offers lush landscape, extraordinary wildlife, and a host of recreational opportunities from its setting within the Santa Cruz River Valley. Hike Mount Wrightson, Arizona's second-highest peak, or spend the day bird-watching in Madera Canyon, ranked as one of the best bird-watching locations in the world. For military history enthusiasts, you'll find the Titan Missile Museum, featuring a deactivated missile still in place inside a missile silo.

Green Valley is a place Arizona Highways has described as "the town too good to die... populated by people who have learned how to live." Green Valley has been selected as one of the best places to retire by Where to Retire and New Choices for Retirement magazines several times. Nestled at the base of the majestic Santa Rita Mountain Range in southern Arizona's beautiful Santa Cruz Valley, Green Valley boasts a high desert elevation of 2,900 feet and enjoys a cooler climate than either Phoenix or Tucson.

Green Valley is among the area's best destinations for both amateur and professional golfers. With a mix of nine public and private courses and year-round mild weather, every day is a good day to play a round here.

Green Valley is a destination for retirees seeking an active lifestyle.
